{"type":"message","id":"0a8ff10b","parentId":"5e034405","timestamp":"2026-02-19T18:51:59.166Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Examining the Roadmap**\n\nI've located the roadmap document, `docs/ROADMAP_V7.md`. My immediate plan is to read through this document thoroughly to validate its contents and the status of the checkboxes. Following that, I'll move on to the code changes, starting with the necessary edits to `src/dmarket/api/client.py`.\n\n\n**Verifying the Roadmap**\n\nI've begun my review of the roadmap. I'm checking each item to ensure it aligns with the current state of development and to prepare for the next steps. After this, I'm eager to dive into the code changes, beginning with the necessary `orjson` integration in `client.py`. I'll proceed with caution, making sure not to introduce any unexpected regressions.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771527119160_64","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs/ROADMAP_V7.md"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":17677,"output":238,"cacheRead":13709,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17915,"cost":{"input":0.035354,"output":0.002856,"cacheRead":0.0027418000000000004,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0409518}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771527113836}}
{"type":"message","id":"8bc4dd7e","parentId":"0a8ff10b","timestamp":"2026-02-19T18:51:59.183Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771527119160_64","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ROADMAP V7.0: COGNITIVE REVOLUTION & HFT SUPREMACY\n\n## Phase 4: Cognitive Architecture (The Brain & MoE)\n### 1. Thinking Mode (Chain-of-Thought)\n*   **Concept:** Implement a mandatory `<thinking>` block before EVERY tool call.\n*   **Mechanism:** The agent must simulate the action mentally, check environment constraints (OS, paths), and validate safety before execution.\n*   **Goal:** Eliminate \"dumb\" errors like `dir not found` or `cargo not found`.\n\n### 2. Mixture of Experts (MoE) - Gemini Family Strategy\n*   **Boss (Gemini 3.1 Pro):** \n    *   *Role:* Strategy Lead, Final Decision Maker.\n    *   *Function:* Synthesizes reports, approves HFT strategy changes, manages risk appetite.\n*   **Techie \"Benjamin\" (Gemini 3 Pro):** \n    *   *Role:* Senior Engineer.\n    *   *Function:* Writes Rust/Python code, designs architecture, implements \"Hard Rebuilds\".\n*   **Librarian \"Harper\" (Gemini 1.5 Pro):** \n    *   *Role:* Knowledge Keeper.\n    *   *Function:* Uses 1M+ context to analyze massive logs, parse documentation (ClawHub/GitHub), and maintain the Knowledge Base.\n*   **QA \"Lucas\" (Gemini 3 Flash):** \n    *   *Role:* Security & Speed.\n    *   *Function:* \"MAKE NO MISTAKES\" checks, real-time Order Book scanning, signature verification.\n\n### 3. Identity & Knowledge\n*   **Skill \"MAKE NO MISTAKES\":** Mandatory pre-execution audit loop by the QA agent.\n*   **Soul & Identity:** Config of `identity.md` and `soul.md` to solidify the \"Cold-Blooded HFT Trader\" persona.\n*   **Smart Search & RAG:** Implementation of a local Vector DB for persistent storage of strategies and insights.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: HFT Supremacy (The Muscle)\n### 1. Rust Network Layer\n*   **Migration:** Move `aiohttp` logic to Rust using `reqwest` + `tokio`.\n*   **Benefit:** Zero-GC networking, true multithreading, <5ms latency globally.\n\n### 2. TUI Dashboard (Ratatui)\n*   **Tool:** Build a CLI dashboard in Rust (`ratatui` crate).\n*   **Features:** Real-time ticker, active orders, wallet balance, log stream.\n\n### 3. Order Book Prediction (ML/Rust)\n*   **Algo:** Implement a lightweight Order Book Imbalance (OBI) predictor in Rust.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Infrastructure, Security & Automation (The Fortress)\n### 1. Automated Councils (Cron Jobs)\n*   **Nightly Councils:** \n    *   *Security:* Audit logs for injection attempts.\n    *   *Business:* Analyze daily P&L and adjust margins.\n*   **Morning Briefing:** Auto-generated Telegram report sent at 08:00 AM.\n\n### 2. Resilience & Defense\n*   **Auto-Backups:** Hourly SQLite snapshots and `git autosync` for code safety.\n*   **Data Sanitization:** Strict input filtering for DMarket API responses to prevent poisoning.\n*   **Prompt Injection Defense:** Active filtering of external signals (News/Telegram).\n\n---\n\n## MANIFESTO\n> \"Я обязуюсь думать перед каждым вызовом инструмента. Ошибка `dir not found` больше невозможна, так как я сначала проверю `os.name` в блоке размышления. Мой код — это продолжение моей мысли.\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771527119181}}
