{"type":"message","id":"76f64c5b","parentId":"fec5588a","timestamp":"2026-02-19T18:52:28.706Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Focusing on Editing Code**\n\nI'm currently elbow-deep in `client.py`, specifically tweaking the `_parse_json_response` function. I'm aiming for tighter error handling, maybe some additional logging. The goal is a more robust client.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771527148518_66","name":"edit","arguments":{"oldText":"    def _parse_json_response(\n        self, response: httpx.Response, path: str\n    ) -> dict[str, Any]:\n        if response.status_code == 204:\n            return {\"status\": \"success\", \"code\": 204}\n        try:\n            return response.json()\n        except Exception:\n            return {\n                \"error\": \"invalid_json\",\n                \"status_code\": response.status_code,\n            }","newText":"    def _parse_json_response(\n        self, response: httpx.Response, path: str\n    ) -> dict[str, Any]:\n        if response.status_code == 204:\n            return {\"status\": \"success\", \"code\": 204}\n        try:\n            return json.loads(response.content)\n        except Exception:\n            return {\n                \"error\": \"invalid_json\",\n                \"status_code\": response.status_code,\n            }","file_path":"src/dmarket/api/client.py"},"thoughtSignature":"CiQBjz1rX2JOOZVHb+gRto1P+aO4oRNxm5SNbnTvR3q4Dvusl34KVAGPPWtful4X7GFzWwU+AF+J01D4Fd+eiYynrPbRp2MWXfGqkRVH/yh10bN0w0J84/mlLHibKVMz6LzcMbBNrSg7CkXu9v8lo3DqV14xNo6rIKLRrgotAY89a18ZPAAyjXZ1HMiEvvfu7UYawhIzbevtQ/25v2NfdBgm32rntJAMC/eP"}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":19265,"output":269,"cacheRead":16744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19534,"cost":{"input":0.038529999999999995,"output":0.003228,"cacheRead":0.0033488000000000003,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.045106799999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timest